==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunder
<hw>Sun"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Sundered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sundering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sundren</ets>, AS. <ets>sundrain</ets> (in
⟦amac⟧<ets>sundrain</ets>, ge<ets>sundrain</ets>), from
<ets>sundor</ets> asunder, separately, apart; akin to D.
<ets>zonder</ets>, prep., without, G. <ets>sonder</ets> separate, as
prep., without, <ets>sondern</ets> but, OHG. <ets>suntar</ets>
separately, Icel. <ets>sundr</ets> asunder, Sw. & Dan.
<ets>s⟦oum⟧nder</ets>, Goth. <ets>sundr⟦omac⟧</ets> alone,
separately.]</ety> <def>To disunite in almost any manner, either by
rending, cutting, or breaking; to part; to put or keep apart; to
separate; to divide; to sever; <as>as, to <ex>sunder</ex> a rope; to
<ex>sunder</ex> a limb; to <ex>sunder</ex> friends.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is <qex>sundered</qex> from the main land by a sandy plain.</q>
<rj><qau>Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sunder
<hw>Sun"der</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To part; to separate.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sunder
<hw>Sun"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Sunder</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>, and cf. <er>Asunder</er>.]</ety> <def>A separation into parts;
a division or severance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In sunder</b></col>, <cd>into parts.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧He
breaketh the bow, and cutteth the spear <xex>in sunder</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Ps. xlvi. 9.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sunder
<hw>Sun"der</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To expose to the sun and
wind.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

